<title>THAILAND: Thai official says finance liquidity woes linger.</title>
<headline>Thai official says finance liquidity woes linger.</headline>
<dateline>BANGKOK 1997-02-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>A senior Bank of Thailand official said on Friday that liquidity problems in the finance sector lingered but the situation, at least for the short-term, was under control.</p>
<p>More finance companies facing tight liquidity had come forward to ask for assistance with funds from the central bank's Financial Institutions Development Fund, the official, who declined to be identified, told Reuters.</p>
<p>But long-term measures were expected to help out any finance firm which might need funds, she said without elaborating.  </p>
<p>&quot;If the situation returned to normal...the public stopped being panicked by rumours, everything should be fine,&quot; she said.</p>
<p>&quot;But if the situation continues to be like this for a long time, it won't be good. The Bank of Thailand is formulating long-term measures to help the sector,&quot; she added.</p>
<p>-- Bangkok newsroom (662) 652-0642</p>
